-- Peru Stocks: Candente, El Brocal, Maple, Southern Copper, Volcan
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-02-06T18:50:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/peru-stocks-candente-el-brocal-maple-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:28 p.m.  Lima  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for the first session in two
weeks, losing 0.3 percent to 22,849.47. The  MSCI All Peru Capped
Index (MXPECAPD)  dropped 0.3 percent to 2,873.14.  Copper and zinc miners fell after metals and U.S. stocks
declined, said Francisco Miranda, an analyst at Lima-based
investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (SMBC)  (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and
copper producer, dropped 1.9 percent to 52 soles.  Southern
Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper producer, fell for
a third session in four, losing 1.8 percent to $34.80. The
company is expected to publish fourth-quarter earnings this
week.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, slid 1.8 percent to $1.10.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VCM\B) 
(VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc and silver producer, declined
1.1 percent to 3.56 soles.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, slumped 3.5 percent to $1.37
after crude declined in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
